body:
Oh, I totally misunderstood the purpose of this issue. Thanks @gianm for your help.
I'm going to further investigate Curator, but until now, it seems difficult to do using LeaderSelector because takeLeadership() must return immediately when a master loses the leadership to release an inter-process mutex which is used in Curator. It means, blocking in takeLeadership() seems to block other overlord nodes from taking the leadership. See the below code.

```
    try
    {
        mutex.acquire();

        hasLeadership = true;
        try
        {
            ...
            listener.takeLeadership(client);
        }
        ...
    }
    ...
    finally
    {
        if ( hasLeadership )
        {
            hasLeadership = false;
            try
            {
                mutex.release();
            }
            ...
        }
    }
```

DurationGranularity doesn't need this check, the construct will throw zero divide error if millis=0

```
  public DurationGranularity(long millis, long origin)
  {
    this.length = millis;
    this.origin = origin % length;
  }
```
